<Prose
  title="Affiliate Disclosure: welanutria"
  description="How welanutria uses affiliate links and what that means for you."
  heading="Affiliate Disclosure"
  updated="July 2026"
>
  <p>welanutria.com ("the site") is reader-supported. Some of the links on this site are affiliate links, and we want to be fully transparent about what that means for you.</p>

  <h2>What affiliate links are</h2>
  <p>An affiliate link is a special link to a product or service on another company's website. If you click one of these links and make a purchase, we may earn a small commission, <strong>at no extra cost to you</strong>. The price you pay is exactly the same whether you use our link or not.</p>

  <h2>How we use them</h2>
  <p>We may include affiliate links in articles, guides and product recommendations, for example when we suggest a protein powder, kitchen scale or blender. Where a page contains affiliate links, we note this clearly at the top of that page.</p>

  <h2>Our promise on recommendations</h2>
  <p class="note"><strong>We only recommend products we believe are genuinely useful.</strong> A commission never changes our opinion. Our recommendations are based on the merits of the product, not on how much we might earn. If we would not suggest it to a friend, we do not put it on the site.</p>

  <h2>Amazon Associates</h2>
  <p>welanutria is a participant in the Amazon Associates Program, an affiliate advertising program designed to provide a way for sites to earn fees by linking to Amazon and affiliated sites. As an Amazon Associate, we earn from qualifying purchases.</p>

  <h2>Other programs</h2>
  <p>We may also take part in other affiliate programs from time to time. In all cases, the same principle applies: links may earn us a commission, at no extra cost to you, and our recommendations remain honest and independent.</p>

  <h2>Why this supports the site</h2>
  <p>Commissions help us keep welanutria free to use, with no sign-up required, while we continue to create free calculators, recipes, food guides and articles. If you find something useful here and choose to buy through our links, thank you: it genuinely helps.</p>

  <h2>Not professional advice</h2>
  <p>Product suggestions are for general information only and are not medical, nutritional or professional advice. Choose what is right for your own needs, and consult a qualified professional where appropriate.</p>

  <h2>Contact</h2>
  <p>Questions about our affiliate relationships? Email <a href="mailto:hello@welanutria.com">hello@welanutria.com</a>.</p>

  <p class="note">This disclosure is provided for transparency and general information, and is not legal advice.</p>
</Prose>
